obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (37197)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes `*. Vide notification No. S.O. 3912(E), dated 30th October, 2019, this Act is made applicable to the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir and the Union territory of Ladakh.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00024_198461_1517807326597&sectionId=37197&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00024_198461_1517807326597
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Terrorist Affected Areas`
  line `(Special Courts) Act, 1984.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India except the State of Jammu and Kashmir*.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall be deemed to have come into force on the 14th day of July, 1984.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (37198)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00024_198461_1517807326597&sectionId=37198&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00024_198461_1517807326597
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,—`
  line
  line `(a) "Code" means the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974);`
  line
  line `(b) "'High Court", in relation to a Special Court, means the High Court within the territorial limits`
  line `of whose jurisdiction such Special Court is proposed to be, or is, established;`
  line
  line `(c) "judicial zone" means a judicial zone constituted under sub-section (1) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(d) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(e) "Public Prosecutor" means a Public Prosecutor or an Additional Public Prosecutor or a Special`
  line `Public Prosecutor appointed under section 9 and includes any person acting under the directions of`
  line `the Public Prosecutor;`
  line
  line `(f) "scheduled offence" means an offence specified in the Schedule being an offence committed`
  line `in a terrorist affected area;`
  line
  line `(g) "Special Court" means a Special Court or an Additional Special Court established under`
  line `section 4;`
  line
  line `(h) "terrorist" means a person who indulges in wanton killing of persons or in violence or in the`
  line `disruption of services or means of communications essential to the community or in damaging`
  line `property with a view to—`
  line
  line `(i) putting the public or any section of the public in fear; or`
  line
  line `(ii) affecting adversely the harmony between different religious, racial, language or regional`
  line `groups or castes or communities; or`
  line
  line `(iii) coercing or overawing the Government established by law; or`
  line
  line `(iv) endangering the sovereignty and integrity of India;`
  line
  line `(i) "terrorist affected area" means an area declared as a terrorist affected area under section 3;`
  line
  line `(j) words and expressions used but not defined in this Act and defined in the Code shall have the`
  line `meanings respectively assigned to them in the Code.`
  line
  line `(2) Any reference in this Act to the Code or any provision thereof shall, in relation to an area in which`
  line `the Code or such provision is not in force, be construed as a reference to the corresponding law or the`
  line `relevant provision of the corresponding law, if any, in force in that area.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (37199)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Declaration of terrorist affected area.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00024_198461_1517807326597&sectionId=37199&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00024_198461_1517807326597
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Central Government is of the opinion that`
  line `offences of the nature specified in the Schedule are being committed in any area by terrorists on such a`
  line `scale and in such a manner that it is expedient for the purpose of coping with the activities of such`
  line `terrorists to have recourse to the provisions of this Act, it may, by notification,--`
  line
  line `(a) declare such area to be a terrorist affected area; and`
  line
  line `(b) constitute such area into a single judicial zone or into as many judicial zones as it may deem`
  line fit.
  line
  line `(2) A notification issued under sub-section (1) in respect of an area shall specify the period during`
  line `which the area shall, for the purposes of this Act, be a terrorist affected area, and where the Central`
  line `Government is of the opinion that terrorists had been committing in that area, from a date earlier than the`
  line `date of issue of the notification, offences of the nature specified in the Schedule on such a scale and in`
  line `such a manner that it is expedient to commence the period specified in the notification from such earlier`
  line `date, the period specified in the notification may commence from that date:`
  line
  line `Provided that--`
  line
  line `(a) no period commencing from a date earlier than six months from the date of publication of the`
  line `notification shall be specified therein; and`
  line
  line `(b) so much of the period specified in such notification as is subsequent to the date of publication`
  line `of the notification shall not, in the first instance, exceed six months, but the Central Government may,`
  line `by notification, extend such period from time to time by any period not exceeding six months at any`
  line `one time, if the Central Government, having regard to the activities of terrorists in such area, is of the`
  line `opinion that it is expedient so to do.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the avoidance of doubts, it is hereby declared that the period specified in a`
  line `notification issued under this section may commence from a date earlier than the date of commencement`
  line `of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (37200)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Establishment of Special Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00024_198461_1517807326597&sectionId=37200&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00024_198461_1517807326597
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purpose of providing for speedy trial of scheduled`
  line `offences committed in a judicial zone, the Central Government may establish, by notification, a Special`
  line `Court in relation to such judicial zone—`
  line
  line `(a) within such judicial zone; or`
  line
  line `(b) if the Central Government having regard to the exigencies of the situation in such judicial`
  line `zone considers it expedient so to do, at any place outside such judicial zone but within the State in`
  line `which such judicial zone is situated.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), if, having regard to the exigencies of the`
  line `situation prevailing in a State, the State Government is of the opinion that it is expedient to establish in`
  line `relation to a judicial zone, or in relation to two or more judicial zones, in the State, an Additional Special`
  line `Court outside the State, for the trial of such scheduled offences committed in the judicial zone or judicial`
  line `zones, the trial whereof within the State—`
  line
  line `(a) is not likely to be fair or impartial or completed with utmost dispatch; or`
  line
  line `(b) is not likely to be feasible without occasioning a breach of peace or grave risk to the safety of`
  line `the accused, the witnesses, the Public Prosecutor and the Judge or any of them; or`
  line
  line `(c) is not otherwise in the interests of justice,`
  line
  line `the State Government may request the Central Government to establish in relation to such judicial zone or`
  line `judicial zones an Additional Special Court outside the State and thereupon the Central Government may,`
  line `after taking into account the information furnished by the State Government and making such inquiry, if`
  line `any, as it may deem fit, establish, by notification, such Additional Special Court at such place outside the`
  line `State as may be specified in the notification.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (37201)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Composition and appointment of Judges of Special Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00024_198461_1517807326597&sectionId=37201&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00024_198461_1517807326597
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Special Court shall be`
  line `presided over by a judge to be appointed by the Central Government with the concurrence of the Chief`
  line `Justice of the High Court.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may also appoint, with the concurrence of the Chief Justice of the High`
  line `Court, Additional judges to exercise jurisdiction in a Special Court.`
  line
  line `(3) A person shall not be qualified for appointment as a Judge or an Additional judge of a Special`
  line `Court unless he is immediately before such appointment a Sessions Judge or an Additional Sessions`
  line `Judge in any State.`
  line
  line `(4) For the removal of doubts, it is hereby provided that the attainment by a person, appointed as a`
  line `Judge or an Additional Judge of a Special Court, of age of superannuation under the rules applicable to`
  line `him in the Service to which he belongs, shall not affect his continuance as such Judge or Additional`
  line Judge.
  line
  line `(5) Where any Additional Judge or Additional Judges is, or are, appointed in a Special Court, the`
  line `Judge of the Special Court may, from time to time, by general or special order, in writing, provide for the`
  line `distribution of business of the Special Court among himself and the Additional Judge or Additional`
  line `Judges and also for the disposal of urgent business in the event of his absence or the absence of any`
  line `Additional Judge.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (37202)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Place of sitting.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00024_198461_1517807326597&sectionId=37202&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00024_198461_1517807326597
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `A Special Court may, if it considers it expedient or desirable so to do, sit for any`
  line `of its proceedings at any place, other than the ordinary place of its sitting, in the State in which it is`
  line `established:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the Public Prosecutor certifies to the Special Court that it is in his opinion necessary`
  line `for the protection of the accused or any witness or otherwise expedient in the interests of justice that the`
  line `whole or any part of the trial should be held at some place other than the ordinary place of its sitting, the`
  line `Special Court may, after hearing the accused, make an order to that effect unless, for reasons to be`
  line `recorded in writing, the Special Court thinks fit to make any other order.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (37203)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Jurisdiction of Special Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00024_198461_1517807326597&sectionId=37203&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00024_198461_1517807326597
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code or in any`
  line `other law, a scheduled offence committed in a judicial zone in a State at any time during the period during`
  line `which such judicial zone is, or is part of, a terrorist affected area shall be triable, whether during or after`
  line `the expiry of such period, only by the Special Court established for such judicial zone in the State:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the period specified under sub-section (2) of section 3 as the period during which`
  line `an area declared by notification under sub-section (1) of that section to be a terrorist affected area`
  line `commences from a date earlier than the date on which such notification is issued, then—`
  line
  line `(a) nothing in the foregoing provisions of this sub-section shall apply to a scheduled offence`
  line `committed in such area in which the whole of the evidence for the prosecution has been taken before`
  line `the date of issue of such notification; and`
  line
  line `(b) all other cases involving scheduled offences committed in such area and pending before any`
  line `court immediately before the date of issue of such notification shall stand transferred to the Special`
  line `Court having jurisdiction under this section and the Special Court to which such proceedings stand`
  line `transferred shall proceed with such cases from the stage at which they were pending at that time.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), if in respect of a case involving a`
  line `scheduled offence committed in any judicial zone in a State, the Central Government, having regard to the`
  line `provisions of sub-section (2) of section 4 and the facts and circumstances of the case and all other relevant`
  line `factors, is of the opinion that it is expedient that such offence should be tried by the Additional Special`
  line `Court established in relation to such judicial zone outside the State, the Central Government may make a`
  line `declaration to that effect:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such declaration shall be made unless the State Government has forwarded to the`
  line `Central Government a report in writing containing a request for making of such declaration.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—Where an Additional Special Court is established in relation to two or more judicial`
  line `zones, such Additional Special Court shall be deemed, for the purposes of this sub-section, to have been`
  line `established in relation to each of such judicial zones.`
  line
  line `(3) A declaration made under sub-section (2) shall not be called in question in any court.`
  line
  line `(4) Where any declaration is made in respect of any offence committed in a judicial zone in a State,`
  line `any prosecution in respect of such offence shall be instituted only in the Additional Special Court`
  line `established in relation to such judicial zone outside the State, and if any prosecution in respect of such`
  line `offence is pending immediately before such declaration in any other court, the same shall stand`
  line `transferred to such Additional Special Court and such Additional Special Court shall proceed with such`
  line `case from the stage at which it was pending at that time.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (37204)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Powers of Special Courts with respect to other offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00024_198461_1517807326597&sectionId=37204&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00024_198461_1517807326597
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) When trying any scheduled`
  line `offence, a Special Court may also try any offence other than the scheduled offence with which the`
  line `accused may, under the Code, be charged at the same trial if the offence is connected with the scheduled`
  line offence.
  line
  line `(2) If, in the course of any trial under this Act, it is found that the accused person has committed any`
  line `offence, the Special Court may, whether such offence is or is not a scheduled offence, convict such person`
  line `of such offence and pass any sentence authorised by law for the punishment thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (37205)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Public Prosecutors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00024_198461_1517807326597&sectionId=37205&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00024_198461_1517807326597
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) For every Special Court, the Central Government shall appoint a person`
  line `to be the Public Prosecutor and may appoint one or more persons to be the Additional Public Prosecutor`
  line `or Additional Public Prosecutors:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may also appoint for any case or class of cases a Special Public`
  line Prosecutor.
  line
  line `(2) A person shall be eligible to be appointed as a Public Prosecutor or an Additional Public`
  line `Prosecutor or a Special Public Prosecutor under this section only if he has been in practice as an Advocate`
  line `for not less than seven years or has held any post, for a period of not less than seven years, under the`
  line `Union or a State, requiring special knowledge of law.`
  line
  line `(3) Every person appointed as a Public Prosecutor or an Additional Public Prosecutor or a Special`
  line `Public Prosecutor under this section shall be deemed to be a Public Prosecutor within the meaning of`
  line `clause (u) of section 2 of the Code, and the provisions of the Code shall have effect accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (37206)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Procedure and powers of Special Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00024_198461_1517807326597&sectionId=37206&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00024_198461_1517807326597
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Special Court may take cognizance of any`
  line `scheduled offence, without the accused being committed to it for trial, upon receiving a complaint of facts`
  line `which constitute such offence or upon a police report of such facts.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a scheduled offence is punishable with imprisonment for a term not exceeding three years`
  line `or with fine or with both, a Special Court may, notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 260 or section 262 of the Code, try the offence in a summary way in accordance with the`
  line `procedure prescribed in the Code and the provisions of sections 263 to 265 of the Code, shall, so far as`
  line `may be, apply to such trial:`
  line
  line `Provided that when, in the course of a summary trial under this sub-section, it appears to the Special`
  line `Court that the nature of the case is such that it is undesirable to try it in a summary way, the Special Court`
  line `shall recall any witnesses who may have been examined and proceed to re-hear the case in the manner`
  line `provided by the provisions of the Code for the trial of such offence and the said provisions shall apply to`
  line `and in relation to a Special Court as they apply to and in relation to a Magistrate:`
  line
  line `Provided further that in the case of any conviction in a summary trial under this section, it shall be`
  line `lawful for a Special Court to pass a sentence of imprisonment for a term not exceeding two years.`
  line
  line `(3) A Special Court may, with a view to obtaining the evidence of any person supposed to have been`
  line `directly or indirectly concerned in, or privy to, an offence, tender a pardon to such person on condition of`
  line `his making a full and true disclosure of the whole circumstances within his knowledge relative to the`
  line `offence and to every other person concerned whether as principal or abettor in the commission thereof,`
  line `and any pardon so tendered shall, for the purposes of section 308 of the Code, be deemed to have been`
  line `tendered under section 307 thereof.`
  line
  line `(4) Subject to the other provisions of this Act, a Special Court shall, for the purpose of trial of any`
  line `offence, have all the powers of a Court of Session and shall try such offence as if it were a Court of`
  line `Session so far as may be in accordance with the procedure prescribed in the Code for the trial before a`
  line `Court of Session.`
  line
  line `(5) Subject to the other provisions of this Act, every case before an Additional Special Court shall be`
  line `dealt with as if such case had been transferred under section 406 of the Code to such Additional Special`
  line Court.
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (37207)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Power of Supreme Court to transfer case.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00024_198461_1517807326597&sectionId=37207&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00024_198461_1517807326597
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `Whenever it is made to appear to the Supreme`
  line `Court that an order under this section is expedient for the ends of justice, it may direct that any particular`
  line `case be transferred from one Special Court to another Special Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (37208)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Protection of witnesses.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00024_198461_1517807326597&sectionId=37208&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00024_198461_1517807326597
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code, all proceedings`
  line `before a Special Court shall be conducted in camera:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the Public Prosecutor so applies, any proceedings or part thereof may be held in`
  line `open court.`
  line
  line `(2) A Special Court may, on an application made by a witness in any proceedings before it or by the`
  line `Public Prosecutor in relation to such witness or on its own motion, take such measures as it deems fit for`
  line `keeping the identity and address of the witness secret.`
  line
  line `(3) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the provisions of sub-section (2), the`
  line `measures which a Special Court may take under that sub-section may include—`
  line
  line `(a) the holding of the proceeding at a protected place;`
  line
  line `(b) the avoiding of the mention of the names and addresses of the witnesses in its orders or`
  line `judgments or in any records of the case accessible to public;`
  line
  line v
  line `(c) the issuing of any directions for securing that the identity and addresses of the witnesses are`
  line `not disclosed.`
  line
  line `(4) Any person who contravenes any direction issued under sub-section (2) shall be punishable with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year and with fine which may extend to one thousand`
  line rupees.
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (37209)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Power to transfer cases to regular courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00024_198461_1517807326597&sectionId=37209&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00024_198461_1517807326597
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `Where after taking cognizance of any offence, a`
  line `Special Court is of opinion that the offence is not a scheduled offence, it shall, notwithstanding that it has`
  line `no jurisdiction to try such offence, transfer the case for trial of such offence to any court having`
  line `jurisdiction under the Code and the court to which the case is transferred may proceed with the trial of the`
  line `offence as if it has taken cognizance of the offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (37210)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title Appeal.
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00024_198461_1517807326597&sectionId=37210&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00024_198461_1517807326597
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code, an appeal shall lie as a matter of`
  line `right from any judgment, sentence or order, not being interlocutory order, of a Special Court to the`
  line `Supreme Court both on facts and on law.`
  line
  line `(2) Except as aforesaid, no appeal or revision shall lie to any court from any judgment, sentence or`
  line `order of a Special Court.`
  line
  line `(3) Every appeal under this section shall be preferred within a period of thirty days from the date of`
  line `the judgment, sentence or order appealed from:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Supreme Court may entertain an appeal after the expiry of the said period of thirty`
  line `days if it is satisfied that the appellant had sufficient cause for not preferring the appeal within the period`
  line `of thirty days.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (37211)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Modified application of certain provisions of the Code.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00024_198461_1517807326597&sectionId=37211&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00024_198461_1517807326597
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in the Code or any other law, every scheduled offence shall be deemed to be a cognizable`
  line `offence within the meaning of clause (c) of section 2 of the Code and "cognizable case" as defined in that`
  line `clause shall be construed accordingly.`
  line
  line `(2) Section 167 of the Code shall apply in relation to a case involving a scheduled offence subject to`
  line `the modifications that—`
  line
  line `(a) the reference in sub-section (1) thereof to "Judicial Magistrate"shall be construed as a`
  line `reference to "Judicial Magistrate or Executive Magistrate";`
  line
  line `(b) the references in sub-section (2) thereof to "fifteen days"`
  line `, "ninety days"and sixty days",`
  line `wherever they occur, shall be construed as references to "thirty days", "one year" and "one year",`
  line `respectively; and`
  line
  line `(c) sub-section (2A) thereof shall be deemed to have been omitted.`
  line
  line `(3) Sections 366 to 371 and section 392 of the Code shall apply in relation to a case involving a`
  line `scheduled offence subject to the modifications that the references to "Court of Session"and "High`
  line `Court", wherever occurring therein, shall be construed as references to "Special Court"and "Supreme`
  line `Court", respectively.`
  line
  line `(4) Nothing in section 438 of the Code shall apply in relation to any case involving the arrest of any`
  line `person on an accusation of having committed a scheduled offence in a terrorist affected area.`
  line
  line `(5) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code, no person accused of a scheduled offence shall,`
  line `if in custody, be released on bail or on his own bond unless—`
  line
  line `(a) the Public Prosecutor has been given an opportunity to oppose the application for such`
  line `release, and`
  line
  line `(b) where the Public Prosecutor opposes the application, the court is satisfied that there are`
  line `reasonable grounds for believing that he is not guilty of such offence and that he is not likely to`
  line `commit any offence while on bail.`
  line
  line `(6) The limitations on granting of bail specified in sub-section (5) are in addition to the limitations`
  line `under the Code or any other law for the time being in force on granting of bail.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15_a:
  sectionId (37212)
  sectionNo 15A
  orderNo 16
  title `Abolition of certain Special Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 45 of 1985, s. 2 (w.e.f. 26-8-1985).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00024_198461_1517807326597&sectionId=37212&sectionno=15A&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00024_198461_1517807326597
obj_root_law_sections_15_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[15A. Abolition of certain Special Courts.—Where the area comprising a judicial zone has ceased`
  line `to be a terrorist affected area and no cases are pending before a Special Court or an Additional Special`
  line `Court established in relation to such judicial zone, the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, abolish such Special Court or Additional Special Court.]`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (37213)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 17
  title `Overriding effect of Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00024_198461_1517807326597&sectionId=37213&sectionno=16&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00024_198461_1517807326597
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) The provisions of this Act shall have effect notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in the Code or any other law, but save as expressly provided in this Act, the`
  line `provisions of the Code shall, in so far as they are not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, apply to`
  line `the proceedings before a Special Court; and for the purpose of the said provisions of the Code, the Special`
  line `Court shall be deemed to be a Court of Session.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the provisions contained in sub-section (1),`
  line `the provisions of sections 326 and 475 of the Code shall, as far as may be, apply to the proceedings before`
  line `a Special Court, and for this purpose any reference in those provisions to a Magistrate shall be construed`
  line `as a reference to the Special Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (37214)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 18
  title Delegation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00024_198461_1517807326597&sectionId=37214&sectionno=17&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00024_198461_1517807326597
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by notification, delegate, subject to such conditions`
  line `as may be specified, all or any of the powers exercisable by it under this Act [except the power under subsection (2) of section 4 and the power under sub-section (2) of section 7] to the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (37215)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 19
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00024_198461_1517807326597&sectionId=37215&sectionno=18&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00024_198461_1517807326597
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `The Supreme Court may, by notification, make such rules, if any, as it`
  line `may deem necessary for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (37216)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 20
  title Saving.
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00024_198461_1517807326597&sectionId=37216&sectionno=19&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00024_198461_1517807326597
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) Nothing in this Act shall affect the jurisdiction exercisable by, or the procedure`
  line `applicable to, any court or other authority under any law relating to the naval, military or air forces or any`
  line `other armed forces of the Union.`
  line
  line `(2) For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that for the purposes of any such law as is referred`
  line `to in sub-section (1), a Special Court shall be deemed to be a Court of ordinary criminal justice.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (37217)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 21
  title `Amendment of Act 1 of 1872.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00024_198461_1517807326597&sectionId=37217&sectionno=20&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00024_198461_1517807326597
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `In the Indian Evidence Act, 1872, after section 111, the`
  line `following section shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"111A.Presumption as to certain offences."--(1) Where a person is accused of having`
  line `committed any offence specified in sub-section (2), in`
  line
  line `(a) any area declared to be a disturbed area under any enactment, for the time being in force,`
  line `making provision for the suppression of disorder and restoration and maintenance of public order;`
  line or
  line
  line `(b) any area in which there has been, over a period of more than one month, extensive`
  line `disturbance of the public peace,`
  line
  line `and it is shown that such person had been at a place in such area at a time when firearms or explosives`
  line `were used at or from that place to attack or resist the members of any armed forces or the forces`
  line `charged with the maintenance of public order acting in the discharge of their duties, it shall be`
  line `presumed, unless the contrary is shown, that such person had committed such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) The offences referred to in sub-section (1) are the following, namely:`
  line
  line `(a) an offence under section 121, section 121A, section 122 or section 123 of the Indian Code`
  line `(45 of 1860);`
  line
  line `(b) criminal conspiracy or attempt to commit, or abetment of, an offence under section 122 or`
  line `section 123 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860)."`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (37218)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 22
  title `Repeal and saving.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00024_198461_1517807326597&sectionId=37218&sectionno=21&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00024_198461_1517807326597
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Terrorist Affected Areas (Special Courts) Ordinance, 1984(9 of`
  line `1984), is hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding such repeal, anything done or any action taken under the said Ordinance shall be`
  line `deemed to have been done or taken under the corresponding provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
